Description: Crowd Sourced News Aggregator
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Before the advent of journalism, those in power wrote the books about history. Their opinions of events have become what we came to accept as fact. These days we have famous syndicated journalists to provide us with their unique views about world happenings. This now is how history is written. If we step out of the proverbial “box” for a moment, we can see that history is repeating itself. Owners of these large media companies push their agendas through mediums they own, newspapers, television news programs, said journalists and the like. This way, they are forming public opinion and until now they have never been policed. Pressrate is a collaborative work in progress that allows the masses to categorize articles, vote up stories that they feel are noteworthy, effectively tailoring a newspapers front page. It allows users to save articles for future reference, rate the journalistic integrity of well known syndicated journalists and citizen journalists alike. One game changing feature is our citizen journalism section where everyday people can anonymously submit newsworthy content and have it voted on, be it a blog post, image, youtube video etc. In these times, everyday citizens record newsworthy material using their point and shoot cameras or even cell phones to shoot video. Pressrate is an outlet or medium for the release of this information to the world. This allows a lone blogger or Pressrate user who submitted something the internet community feels is important or newsworthy (and voted up) to reach the front page with his/her post/content positioned right beside a story from a large news source. This provides a medium and opinion forming power to an average Joe who possesses facts or insight on any given event. For example, things that large media companies may not want you to see. One blatant example was the media blackout we saw in the first few weeks of the Occupy Wall Street movement. Also, often times, comments left on news article pages that are critical of the author or source are immediately deleted. We hope to be a centralized location for user comments, opinions or insights written about news stories.  We vow and pledge to NEVER delete anything (regardless of how much we may disagree with it). So many opinions, objectives and motives behind many article sources today necessitated a crowd sourced method of rating news articles, journalists and news sources to best assist the public when trying to decipher which of these to take seriously (Coming soon) We at Pressrate are currently developing an intuitive news aggregater. We learn which news topics and stories you like to read and use this data to present you with a section where you will find headlines that are sure to interest you. By The Founder- An anonymous soul - yearning to cut out the BS and get fed information in a proper manner minus the techno babble, personal opinions and agendas of those (currently) in charge.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment, Video

Description: Rayeman Elements manufactures, develops, and distributes innovative technology to produce environmentally friendly products.
Full Description: Rayeman Elements manufactures, develops, and distributes innovative technology to produce environmentally friendly products for the ethanol industry. Its Rayeman Bulk Densification Equipment utilizes patented technology to provide sustainable solutions for range cattle, as well as other species' feed, renewable energy, and shipping purposes. This ground-breaking system processes 100% distillers' or brewers' grain with no added fillers or binders, using only heating, cooling, and 3-dimensional pressure through its unique technology.   This patented technology provides the opportunity to bulk densify virtually any product introduced, reducing the material by up to 70%, forming a cube, pellet, or log. Rayeman Elements has recently completed a sale of two ground-breaking Rayeman Compression Dryers (RCD) to Lincolnway Energy in Nevada, Iowa. The RCD's patented technology safely and efficiently converts wet grain to premium dry grain, in a process that yields the benefits of the reduction of emissions, elimination of explosions, a smaller footprint, and significantly lower capital outlay and operating costs than conventional dryer systems.  The Rayeman Compression Dryer is designed to be flexible, dependent on desired output and dryness levels. The barrel and screw arrangements can be hooked up in series or in a parallel configuration and can be connected in series to existing conventional drying systems to increase capacity and quality.
